(1) ANN Visual Video from 3 Blue 1 Brown
---------------------------------------
ANN stands for Artificial Neural Network.
It is inspired by the human brain’s neuron structure.
The network contains input, hidden, and output layers.
Each neuron is connected using weights and biases.
Input data moves layer by layer through the network.
Hidden layers help detect patterns from data.
The output layer gives the final prediction result.
ANN learns by adjusting weights during training.
It is widely used in machine learning and deep learning.
Example applications include image recognition and speech recognition.

