(2) Gradient Descent, How Neural Networks Learn | Chapter 2, Deep Learning
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Gradient Descent is a learning algorithm used in neural networks.
Its main goal is to reduce prediction error.
The network first makes a prediction.
A cost function measures how wrong the prediction is.
Gradient tells the direction of maximum error reduction.
Weights and biases are updated step by step.
The process repeats many times during training.
Over time, prediction accuracy improves.
It works like a ball rolling downhill toward the lowest point.
Gradient Descent is one of the core concepts in deep learning.

