3) What is Backpropagation Really Doing? | Chapter 3, Deep Learning
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Backpropagation is the main training process of neural networks.
It helps the network learn from mistakes.
The process starts after calculating prediction error.
Error information moves backward through the layers.
The output layer is adjusted first.
Hidden layers are corrected one by one afterward.
Important weights receive larger adjustments.
Less important connections receive smaller changes.
Backpropagation works together with Gradient Descent.
This process helps neural networks become more accurate over time.


